The obtained value of the ε3 = 0.65 meV coincides with the activation energies for the variable range hopping conduction found in ZnO thin films to be below 1 meV52,53, and thus corresponds to the activation energy of the Mott’s variable range hopping following T−1/4 law in the low-temperature range 90–10 K. The evaluated values of the average hopping distance R¯hop,Mott\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
